(20, 208, 'Emmanuel Ayodele', 'ayodele373@gmail.com', '08132898555', '21, Hassan Idowu Str, Aguda, Surulere', NULL, '26', 'male', NULL, 'cv_upload/i0lbVXqroALhk8UYuqpaP6NhrIxAwWXe5qjvs1i1.pdf', '<p>I am an Electrical and Electronics Engineering graduate of University of Lagos, a prospective Artificial Intelligence (AI) specialist with proven analytical and innovative skills, looking to develop my skills and abilities to help solve social, health and economic related problems (most particularly in developing countries) by optimizing decision processes using relevant contemporary descriptive, predictive and prescriptive data models, thereby achieving automation. My goal is always to use a data-driven approach (with AI at its core) to solve all kinds of problem. In my DNA, lies the power to draw actionable insights from organic data. I have been very fortunate to work as a Data Analyst with Branch International, a reputable Fintech startup headquartered in SanFrancisco, California where I was saddled with the key responsibilities of using various tools and software for data collection/gathering, data wrangling/manipulation, data visualization, data modeling, presentation and process automation. These tools include but are not limited to SQL, Python(particularly core libraries such as Pandas, Numpy, Scipy, Matplotlib, scikit-learn etc.), Power BI, Tableau, Periscope Data, Microsoft excel, Google sheets and Google Slides. I am also very familiar with the ubiquitous Amazon RDS. Additionally, during my service year as a National Youth Corps Member in 2017, I worked as a Data Officer with the World Health Organization (WHO) in Ondo state, Nigeria where I helped in the gathering, cleaning and analysis of health data from all local governments during the immunization period conducted on children between (0-5years). This position perfectly aligns with my goals and will offer me opportunities to make a difference in this rapidly changing world. If accepted, I would apply all th