(136, 506, 'Olarewajiu Aoayee Okiei', 'ayeherodotus@yahoo.com', '07033145737', '2, Odogbolu Street, Palmgrove, Lagos.', NULL, '36', 'male', 'married', 'cv_upload/C8xjHZ2bNdYP25aeJsIK5frJ8CN4pH9CIqLdnDpW.zip', NULL, NULL, '2020-07-24 15:55:04', '2020-07-24 15:55:04', 3, 'profile_photo/TYvUQbR4waOFOPP6FLYzxKeeZx5uOGJ4d6vv4UzX.jpeg', NULL),
(137, 507, 'Mary Umiom', 'maryumiom11@gmail.com', '07065283242', 'Before,  Ajay,  Lagos', NULL, '28', 'female', 'single', 'cv_upload/eTdF9LX1sCf2yxBZPpSGllAW2paIRzYDAfcNM8uX.zip', '<hr />\r\n<p>Dear Sir/Ma,</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>APPLICATION FOR THE POSITION OF A SALES INTERN</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am writing to express my strong interest in your organization for the position of a sales intern. I am a graduate of Communication Arts from University of Uyo.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I have developed excellent communication skills and creative skills through my degree as well as customer service and administrative skills through my work experiences.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would relish the opportunity to take these skills to such prestigious and forward-thinking organization.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enclosed is my detailed resume that highlights my work experiences, education, training and skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I look forward to hearing from you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yours Sincerely,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mary Umiom</p>', NULL, '2020-07-24 16:55:11', '2020-07-24 16:55:11', 3, 'profile_photo/coVZGwDos9ZjQow9Ny9DxOw30ou31thH0cQ6KVT7.jpeg', 'profile_video/mAJEZSUjnnochVgnFwcpC1akV1dernTtcf3Ul5Ns.zip'),
(138, 512, 'Temitayo Ogunmola', 'tayoojoogunmola@gmail.com', '08061344128', NULL, NULL, '30', 'male', 'single', 'cv_upload/V0qDtcPdAr9pasN0TIULiCKtd8vh2p2nerY1PBha.docx', '<p>Dear Human Resources Manager,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the enclosed resume, I would like to express my sincere interest in the&nbsp;<strong>Role of Technical Sales &amp; Marketing&nbsp;</strong>position available at your company. As a successful professional with over 4 years&rsquo; experience in negotiating with clients and building new sales pipelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I hold a bachelor&#39;s and master&rsquo;s degree from University of Lagos in Geography and Planning. My education as a geographer involved a detailed study of the principles of technical analysis and risk models. I learned to read chart patterns and determine likely infection points for securities. Fundamental analysis also played a key role in my education, and I am capable of data processing and representation - using required tools / software such as ANOVA, SPSS, and Excel charts to represent data for easy analysis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At&nbsp;<strong>989 Workspace&nbsp;</strong>where I worked at the Business Development Manager<strong>,</strong> I performed all duties allocated to me as a Business Development Manager. I increased sales through a combination of marketing and joint effort with various different strategies.&nbsp;&nbsp;I secured partnership with Business Day and other companies. I followed through with each lead referred to us from the marketing department and converted them to customers. I took potential leads on a tour to our various locations. I monitored all of our locations and ensured our partners followed our business brands guide and operations. I Managed other sales/community managers&#39; sales process and helped them within their various sales processes. I did a SWOT Analysis for both the company and that of our competitors to know how to best fit our pricing system against our competitors and what extra valve can we provide to our customers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At&nbsp;<strong>Bmitch Panache Consulting</strong>, I performed all duties allocated to me as a Key Account Officer/sales Manager. I effectively represented the manager when he was not available at meetings and networking events. I worked with all business partners generating revenues and also monitor each clients and customer satisfaction. I attended to the needs of every client I worked with. I ensured to listen to every client&#39;s needs and provide customer support. I provide customer support all through the sales process and after they use our services too.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>At MGIG Global Services</strong>, I managed people, and responsibilities from office to warehouse effectively. I sourced for new clients in need for our products/services. I was tasked to make cold calls regularly to generate new business. I went to the site to ensure the products are delivered according to the client&rsquo;s requirements. I Attended Oil &amp; Gas themed events sourcing out leads and possible collaborations.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At <strong>Triumph Properties Investment,</strong> I negotiated deals and ensured there was an MOU to cover the company&#39;s interest. I sent invoices to clients for payment. I took clients on a tour to see available properties of their choice. I ensured the properties are in good shape before the clients come for a tour. I sent emails and followed up with each client.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am thankful for your time and consideration of my application. As you continue the hiring process for the Business Development Manager position, I would be delighted to communicate my other accomplishments and career goals in person. I am also looking forward to future correspondence as I would love to find out more about the expectations that you have for your business developers and how I could best meet them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ogunmola Temitayo</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<