(173, 575, 'Eniola', 'eniolaadesanya1997@gmail.com', '09013609102', '7 forolagba street ifako gbagada', NULL, '23', 'female', 'single', 'cv_upload/52d50984bc1b21b5f7dc4829a736559b.pdf', '<p>I am a recent graduate of Business Administration from University of Lagos and I&rsquo;m concentrating on the sales corporate finance and business in general. In addition to my degree I have a membership Certificate of Associate Accounting Technician (AAT) and also pursuing a membership Certificate of Institute of Chartered Accountant of Nigeria (Final Paper). &nbsp;Over the year, have been able to develop and coach myself through a finance lecturing program organized by Allison, CFI and several platforms dealing with corporate finances so as to familiarize myself with the finance industry.&nbsp; Amidst this is my current preparation for a CFA Institute Foundation Program, which will help me bridge the gap of my basic theoretical knowledge of finance with the understanding of the finance service industry as well as contributing to change in the Financial and Business Market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My classroom experiences have provided me with detailed knowledge of financial market and its industry Institutions and enhanced my interest in pursuing a business and &nbsp;financial Career. I feel that an Internship with Snapnet&nbsp;would be a logical next step in my development as a&nbsp;Business and financial Consultant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My main interest in joining Snapnet&nbsp;stems from its impressive Technology organized structure and function. The prestige boutique firm has the best capture for &nbsp;grooming young talent individuals in the state of technology&nbsp;as well as managing its employees well&nbsp; through its believe and&nbsp; values that has been embedded in the organization. I feel the firm&rsquo;s objective, mission, vision and well established atmosphere and work environment for an internship program which will provide me with an invaluable experience to complement with my studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I believe I would succeed in the firm&rsquo;s exciting and motivated environment and that my strong work ethic, ability and passion would make me a valuable asset to your firm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I would prefer to work as a sales technology intern. However, I&rsquo;m willing to consider any position that you offer to me. Thank you for your consideration, and I look forward to speaking with you in the near future.&nbsp;</p>', 'adesanya_SPC_eniolaesther7_SPC_forolagbastreet_SPC_ifako-gbagada_SPC_lagos_SPC_telephone:09013609102|email:eniolaadesanya1997@gmail_SPC_compersonalinformationdateofbirth:22ndmarch1997sex:femalenationality:nigerianmaritalstatus:singlepersonalprofileaself-motivated_SPC_sharp-mindedandgrowingprofessionalseekinganopportunitytoworkwithareputableorganization_SPC_toacquirerelevantandsubstantialskillswithwhichicanactualizemydreamsofbeingawell-roundedprofessionalandaddvalueswithinandoutsidemyspace_SPC_education&qualificationsnationalyouthservicecorpikoroduseniorgrammarschool_SPC_lagos-2020b_SPC_sc_SPC_honsbus_SPC_admin_SPC_(2ndclassupperdivision)–universityoflagos-2019associateaccountingtechnician–aat-2015associatecharteredaccountant-aca(inview_SPC_finalpaper)cfainstitutefoundationprogram-cfa(inview)skillsandvalueofferingproficiencyintheuseofmsofficetools;strongworkethicsandtimemanagementskills;analyticalandinquisitivemind;abilitytolearnfastandworkwithminimalsupervision;teamplayerwithgoodinterpersonalandcommunicationskills;workexperiencemarketing_SPC_accessbankplc_SPC_akoka_SPC_barigalagos-volunteerrole-2018ikoroduseniorgrammarschool(financial&bookkeepingtutor)-nysc-2020leadershipexperienceassistantsecretary-corpsd’eliteunilag_SPC_teamleader-citizenship&leadershiptrainingcentre_SPC_rotaryclubrefereesavailableonrequest_SPC_', '2020-07-30 21:42:40', '2020-07-30 21:42:40', 3, 'profile_photo/gp37Z9WVD648H06KpLtj1bmkZncDm8r9CBPlqque.jpeg', 'profile_video/jHgobr8Rl6rN7SHYNYiUm9GsyvYXhaJFPVBowzHK.mp4'),
(174, 590, 'Khadijat Olanipekun', 'khadijatolanipekun@gmail.com', '08188657772', '32,  Femi  Bamigbelu  street,  opposite  Nigeria  Army Dog center,  command,  Ipaja,  Lagos  state.', NULL, '19', 'female', 'single', 'cv_upload/206b5dee2583b6eb23d2e6e73f2b3765.pdf', '<p>Human Resource Team,&nbsp;<br />\r\nSnapnet,&nbsp;<br />\r\nLagos, Nigeria.<br />\r\n30th August, 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dear HR Manager,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>APPLICATION FOR SALES AND MARKETING INTERN<br />\r\nI am Khadijat Olanipekun, a graduate of Bio-chemistry with commendable academic records and reputable character. I am energetic and an highly&nbsp; dedicated individual with undying zeal for excellence and business professionalism. I have strong financial analytic and quantitative analytic planning skills. I am excellent in both writing and communication skills. I can thrive well in a fast learning organization.&nbsp;<br />\r\nI am also a diploma holder in computer science and have participated in series of engagements such as humanitarian volunteering and other socio-economic engagement that has built and deepen my development on intrapersonal relation needed to excel as a sales personnel and a Business administrator. I have the passion for getting into details to identify root cause of issues and create innovative solutions. I am very much convinced that I would be an invaluable addition into the workforce as an Intern for Snapnet specifically in promoting effective and efficient atmosphere in line with the organizational Culture and in delivery of specified objectives that promotes the overall objectives of the business itself in ensuring accountability, transparency and business professionalism that increase the business qualitative and quantitative values. I therefore look forward to be considered for this position as a Sales and Marketing Intern and also, opportunities to learn from other highly qualified business professionals in Snapnet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regards<br />\r\nKhadijat Olayinka Olanipekun