(331, 904, 'Kayode-Adeoye Mayowa', 'maytoks2000@gmail.com', '09060986935', '21 adetayo osho street, akoka, lagos.', NULL, '26', 'male', 'single', 'cv_upload/8e37078574d1556a8aca7894716ab197.pdf', '<p>The Hiring Manager,<br />\r\nRE: Application for Data Scientist<br />\r\nDear Hiring manager,<br />\r\nAs a young and motivated individual, I am extremely interested in applying for the advertised position of Data Scientist.<br />\r\nIn December 2017, I completed an internship role at Telnet Nigeria Limited where I was charged with the responsibility of ensuring timely reception and delivery of business through administrative, ICT and operational support. This has exposed me to the inner workings of delivering value to businesses which I believe is essential to thrive.<br />\r\nWith regards to my ability to meet the specific requirements of this job:<br />\r\n&bull; Graduate with B Sc. In Engineering: A Second-class upper graduate of Computer Engineering with a major in Networking and took courses in Management and Entrepreneurship and Corporate Governance.<br />\r\n&bull; Experience in Procurement and Technical Sales Engineering: Brand Character is the most important variable in a company&rsquo;s marketing strategy. Had a Polycom training at Telnet Nigeria where I learnt the rudiments of selling one&rsquo;s brand, portraying the brand of the company and its products in the best light possible and in line with company&rsquo;s values. I am currently working with Beyond Energy Resources Limited (A Procurement company for Chevron and Addax) where I am assigned to the technical sales department where I am responsible with providing quotes and working on bids and ensuring the items get to Client&rsquo;s warehouse in compliance with local and international law.<br />\r\nI am currently exploring the field of engineering procurement and supply chain management.<br />\r\nListed below are the duties performed by me as a Procurement Engineer and Sales Analyst.<br />\r\n- I provide clients with sales advice and support. - I prepare tenders, proposals and quotations. - I provide pre-sales and post-sales support. - I negotiate contracts, terms and conditions. - I review costs and sales performances - I write report and sales literature - I provide product education and advice - I manage relationship with OEM&#39;S and Clients<br />\r\n-I make sure I pay prompt attention to details or requirements of technical Items such as Valves, tubing, gaskets, earplugs, cables flanges, bolts, generators, circuit breakers and many more depending on industry.<br />\r\n&bull; Good Interpersonal skills and Relationship Management: Being the Assistant Editor at STAN (Story Tellers Association of Nigeria, Unilag chapter), I scrutinize reports, stories and poems and make the necessary adjustments and send emails to lists of members and guests in the most hospitable manner, pre and post training sessions with the goal of preserving the cordial relationship between the organization and client base and also my duty as a technical sales engineer has sharpened my interpersonal relationship skills as well as dealing with different races.<br />\r\n&bull; Proficiency in Microsoft Suite: I prepared technical reports on a weekly basis for five years at University of Lagos using MS Office tools like Word, Excel and Power-point. I have experience in data analysis using Tableau and Power BI. I designed templates for the company to keep tracks of OTD, OEM lists, bid closing date, RFQ summary sheet and also to keep track of profit margin.<br />\r\n&bull; Experience in Networking and Telecommunications: My role as IT Helpdesk Support Officer at NNPC, AFC Lagos and TELNET Nigeria Limited involves managing and troubleshooting the network infrastructure and computers installed with Windows 10 to ensure timely reception and delivery of business.<br />\r\n&bull;Experience in IT Support: Variety is the spice of life and with a background in engineering , I took it upon myself to remain updated in the IT sphere. I am proficient in using python for data analysis as well as deploying and managing cloud infrastructure.<br />\r\nI understand that you&rsquo;ll be receiving a large number of applications for this role, however, I believe my motivation and pre-existing skills will allow me fit into your work environment.<br />\r\nThanking you in advance for your consideration.<br />\r\nKayode-Adeoye Mayowa</p>', 'kayode-adeoyemayowa21_SPC_adetayooshostreet_SPC_akoka_SPC_lagos_SPC_nigeria+234(0)9060986935maytoks2000@gmail_SPC_comlinkedinprofilekayode-adeoyemayowaisavibrantyoungnigerianwithanunswervingmindsetaboutatarget_SPC_iamresponsibleandstriveforexcellenceinmyeverydaylife_SPC_determinedandcreative_SPC_results-drivencomputerengineerprofessionalwithimpressiveanalyticalandtechnicalsupportabilities_SPC_iamenterprisingandiconstantlyimproveonmyselfandopentolearningeducation_SPC_universityoflagos_SPC_lagos_SPC_nigeria_SPC_•b_SPC_sc_SPC_computerengineering_SPC_october2018_SPC_secondclassupperdivision_SPC_yabacollegeoftechnology_SPC_lagos_SPC_nigeria_SPC_•nd_SPC_computerengineering_SPC_september2013_SPC_uppercreditcoursespythonfordatascience(ibm)ciscocertifiednetworkassociate(udemy)analyzingandvisualizingdatawithmicrosoftexcel_SPC_riceuniversityviacourseraaugust2019–october2019marketanalytics_SPC_universityofvirginiaviacourserafebruary2020–april2020machinelearningwithpython(ibm)knowledgeandskillsdataanalysisandvisualizationusingexcel_SPC_tableauandpowerbitechnicalandnetworksupportengineerandprojectmanagementbiddingofcontractsandprocurementexcellentcommunicationskillsbothorallyandinwritingproficientinmicrosoftofficetoolscctvinstallation_SPC_routerandswitchconfigurationgoodknowledgeofcomputerhardwareandsoftwareengineeringfundamentalsexperiencesupplychainengineerandsalesanalyst_SPC_beyondenergyresourceslimited–lagos_SPC_nigeriamarch2019–april2020beyondenergyresourceslimitedisanengineeringprocurementcompanywithmajorfocusintheoiland