(30, '601bb6a0b16e2', 'SOLUTION SALES EXECUTIVE-Abuja', '<p><strong>Job Summary</strong><br />\r\nSnapnet Nigeria requires a Solution Sales Professional for the Public sector to cover<br />\r\nsoftware/hardware opportunities in the Government and Non-Government Sectors, a highly<br />\r\nstrategic position in the company as role will be responsible for showcasing and driving the sales of<br />\r\nSnapnet&rsquo;s solutions in these sectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Job Description</strong><br />\r\n&bull; Understanding customers&rsquo; diverse, specific business needs and applying product knowledge<br />\r\nto meet those needs.<br />\r\n&bull; Presenting and demonstrating Snapnet solutions to technical and business decision makers<br />\r\nin the industry<br />\r\n&bull; Identifying and developing new business through networking, courtesy and follow-up<br />\r\ncalls<br />\r\n&bull; Developing effective sales plans using sales methodology<br />\r\n&bull; Ensuring quality of service by developing a thorough and detailed knowledge of technical<br />\r\nSpecifications and other features of Snapnet&rsquo;s systems and processes, and then<br />\r\ndocumenting them.<br />\r\n&bull; Preparing and delivering customer presentations and demonstrations of the software,<br />\r\narticulately and confidently<br />\r\n&bull; Maintaining awareness and keeping abreast of constantly changing software and hardware<br />\r\nsystems and peripherals<br />\r\n&bull; Providing technical advice to customers on all aspects of the installation and use of<br />\r\ncomputer<br />\r\nsystems and networks, both before and after the sale<br />\r\n&bull; Advising on software features and how they can be applied to assist in a variety of contexts<br />\r\n&bull; Meeting sales targets set by managers and contributing to team targets<br />\r\n&bull; Networking with existing customers to maintain links and promote additional<br />\r\nproducts and upgrades<br />\r\n&bull; Responding to tender documents, writing proposals, reports and supporting literature<br />\r\n&bull; Managing your own task to organize and prioritize daily and weekly goals<br />\r\n&bull; Contributing to team or progress meetings and updating Management<br />\r\n&bull; Identifying opportunities across the sectors covered and prioritizing to<br />\r\nachieve best results.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong><br />\r\n&bull; Candidate is expected to possess vast knowledge in Public sector<br />\r\n&bull; Candidate is expected to perform independent research and analysis on Snapnet and its<br />\r\nproducts and services<br />\r\n&bull; Excellent demonstrations and Presentation skills.<br />\r\n&bull; Good Pre-sales experience<br />\r\n&bull; Ability to identify business opportunities and proffer solutions that are of value to our<br />\r\ncustomers through our products and services<br />\r\n&bull; Solid Territory Management and Account planning skills<br />\r\n&bull; Ability to identify potential customers (customer acquisition management) and retain them<br />\r\nas esteemed Snapnet clients<br />\r\n&bull; Candidate should possess leadership skills and ability to work within a local and virtual team<br />\r\n&bull; Experience in working with local technology companies as business partners<br />\r\n&bull; Ability to work under pressure, to multitask, to focus and to deliver.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 2, 'Negotiable', 'Negotiable', 'Abuja', 244, '2021-02-08', '4', 1, 3, 2, 0),
(31, '601bb74207799', 'PRE-SALES ENGINEER-Abuja', '<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Pre-Sales Engineer (PSE) provides technical support to the sales team for positioning Snapnet&rsquo;s IT solutions to all customers/prospects. The PSE is an integral part of the sales team and the technical leader during the entire sales cycle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Pre-Sales Engineer will work individually and as part of a team to establish the business and technical value of Snapnet&rsquo;s products, solutions, and services to meet customer specific and requirements. In your role as a trusted advisor for customers, you will collaborate with sales, consulting, and product management resources to ensure our technical solutions address customer needs and exceed the expectations of end users, management, and Tech.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Presales technical support to the sales team, prospects, and clients</li>\r\n	<li>Lead product presentations and demos, as well as proof of concepts</li>\r\n	<li>Provide technical expertise in Snapnet&rsquo;s solutions, inclusive of how they can help our customers monetize their business better and improve their operations.</li>\r\n	<li>Lead technical responses to RFIs, RFQs, RFPs, and other customer requests</li>\r\n	<li>Serve as the technical liaison between clients, sales team, and the internal technical and product experts, including Professional Services, Product Management, Managed Services, and Operations.</li>\r\n	<li>Lead technical pre-sales activities.</li>\r\n	<li>Work closely with Technical, Sales/Marketing and Product teams to close new deals and cross sell to grow the sales pipeline.</li>\r\n	<li>Scope, create and deliver technical presentations and product demonstrations focusing on detailed feature capabilities and highlighting the business value of the solution to customers.</li>\r\n	<li>Able to differentiate Snapnets&rsquo; products and services and build relationship with customers</li>\r\n	<li>Map customer requirements to current and future features to ensure a clear representation of how Snapnets&rsquo; solutions address the customer needs</li>\r\n	<li>Lead the build and execution of customized Snapnets&rsquo; solution demonstrations.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide training to sales team on solution architectures, product features and enhancements to existing products</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Skills and Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>B.S. in Computer Science, Software or Engineering</li>\r\n	<li>5+ years of experience in Information Technology</li>\r\n	<li>Extensive experience in a Technical Support/pre-sales role</li>\r\n	<li>Experience managing complex business relationships.</li>\r\n	<li>A background in or deep familiarity with the IT Services space, demonstrating deep industry knowledge and ability to elevate conversations to business needs and be viewed as a trusted advisor.</li>\r\n	<li>Willingness to travel to customer sites as directed by sales management</li>\r\n	<li>Skilled in virtual presentations, online web demos, remote sales processes</li>\r\n	<li>Vibrant, self-motivated, and energetic attitude; willingness to perform and get things done</li>\r\n	<li>Analytical, self-driven, energetic, team worker, creative, customer focus</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to manage customers&rsquo; expectations and communications</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent oral and written communication skills and excellent presentation skills\r\n	<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', 2, 'Negotiable', 'Negotiable', 'Abuja', 244, '2021-02-08', '4', 1, 3, 2, 0),
